# File: README
# Description: Quick-start guide on how to use 'qemu-img' to create disk images. 
#

#
# Title: Operating on a '.qcow2' disk image with size 32GiB
#

# 1. Create
```bash
$ qemu-img create -f qcow2 mydisk.qcow2 32G
```

# 2. Resize
```bash
$ qemu-img create mydisk.qcow2 64G
``

# 3. Convert
```bash
$ qemu-img convert -f qcow2 -O vdi mydisk.qcow2 mydisk.vdi
```
